<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-02-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-02-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">738.39/325: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-26T14:00:00-05:00">February 26, 1938—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>31. Fiscal representative informs me that check for $250,000 made out to
                            order of the Government of the Republic of Haiti at the National City
                            Bank of New York and endorsed by Mr. George Léger, has been handed to
                            him for deposit, representing the first payment by Dominican Republic to
                            Haitian Government in accordance with agreement of January 31st.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>